%I A395606 #13 May 11 2026 22:24:58
%S A395606 4,136,3044224,28331015385750962176,
%T A395606 22739789572769337332777045784577687155058301197802908155904
%N A395606 Number of involutions (elements of order <= 2) in the n-th iterated wreath product of S_3.
%C A395606 a(n) = sum of dimensions of all irreducible complex representations of the n-th iterated wreath product W_n, where W_0 = S_3 and W_{n+1} = W_n wr S_3.
%C A395606 The equivalence follows from the Frobenius-Schur theorem: since all wreath iterates of S_3 are totally orthogonal (all Frobenius-Schur indicators equal +1), the number of involutions equals sum of dim(rho) over all irreps rho.
%C A395606 The group W_n has order 6^((3^(n+1)-1)/2) and acts naturally on 3^(n+1) points (the vertices of the infinite rooted ternary tree truncated at depth n+1). It arises as the Galois group of the n-th iterate of the polynomial x^3 - x - 1 over Q, under the arboreal Galois representation.
%C A395606 a(n) grows like exp(c * 3^n * log(3^n)) for a constant c > 0, intermediate between the group order (exp(O(3^n))) and the number of elements (which equals the group order).
%F A395606 a(n) = a(n-1)^3 + 3 * |W_{n-1}| * a(n-1) for n >= 1 where |W_n| = 6^((3^(n+1)-1)/2).
%F A395606 If b(n) = a(n)/|W_n| is the involution density, then b(n) = b(n-1)^3 * |W_{n-1}|^2 + 3*b(n-1).
%e A395606 a(0) = 4: S_3 has 4 involutions: {e, (12), (13), (23)}.
%e A395606 a(1) = 136: W_1 = S_3 wr S_3 (order 1296) has 136 involutions. Decomposition: 4^3 = 64 from sigma=e (each h_j an involution), plus 3*6*4 = 72 from sigma=transposition (h_2 = h_1^{-1}, h_3 involution).
%e A395606 a(2) = 3044224: W_2 = (S_3 wr S_3) wr S_3 (order 13060694016) has 3044224 involutions. Check: 136^3 + 3*1296*136 = 2515456 + 528768 = 3044224.
%o A395606 (PARI) for(n=0,5,a=4;g=6;for(k=1,n,t=a;a=a^3+3*g*a;g=g^3*6); print1(a, ", "))
%o A395606 (Python)
%o A395606 def a(n):
%o A395606     ii, gg = 4, 6
%o A395606     for _ in range(n):
%o A395606         ii, gg = ii**3 + 3*gg*ii, gg**3 * 6
%o A395606     return ii
%Y A395606 Cf. A000085 (involutions in S_n, the non-iterated case).
%Y A395606 Cf. A000106 (related wreath product enumerations).
%Y A395606 Cf. A001006 (Motzkin numbers, arising in S_n involution generating functions).
%K A395606 nonn,easy,new
